AU  - Vincent, Daniel R.
T1  - Dynamic Auctions
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297542
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 57
IS  - 1
SP  - 49
EP  - 61
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - A dynamic trading game is examined in which two uninformed buyers engage in Bertrand-like competition to attempt to purchase a single object of uncertain quality from an informed seller. It is shown that there exists a unique perfect sequential equilibrium. The game is compared to an analogous bargaining game in which a single uninformed buyer makes offers to a single seller. Despite the fact that in the equilibrium of the competitive game, buyers compete away their surplus, it is shown that sellers can often gain a higher ex ante surplus in the bargaining game.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297542
ER  - 



